#### Micro-Zones & Tactical Flow

- **The Purge Grate (Center):** Player wake-up. Flanked by two massive cylindrical glass Decon Chambers (primary Anchor Points). Players use Vault-Boost over control consoles to create distance from Scrap-Walkers.
- **The Observation Deck (North):** Elevated metal catwalk overlooking the spawn, accessed by two steep stairways. Introduces verticality immediately—run up, force machines to follow, dive over the railing to gap pursuit. Stairways are ideal Momentum Slide practice inclines. Fabricator Anchor Point lives here.
- **The Security Checkpoint (South):** Cluttered bottleneck (luggage scanners, riot barricades). Houses the *Scrap-Pistol* and *Trench-Gun* wallbuys, Necro-Pulse perk, and the **Vitae Splicer** (2,000 Scrap to swap Blood Arts). High-risk: early perk/art grabs can trap the player if a machine climbs from the floor vent behind them.

#### Gates / Obstacles

- **Gate A (Left):** Zone 2A Bio-Wing — 750 Scrap.
- **Gate B (Right):** Zone 2B Industrial Wing — 750 Scrap.
- Players choose which wing to open first with early Scrap.

#### Machine Ingress

| Ingress | Location | Behavior |
|---------|----------|----------|
| Vent 1 — Shattered Skylight | Above Observation Deck | Dramatic spawn; Hunter-Killers drop onto the catwalk |
| Vent 2 & 3 — Deck Walls | Observation Deck walls | Standard vents; Scrap-Walkers pry metal grating apart |
| Vent 4 — Floor Grate | Security Checkpoint | Machines crawl from below; forces footing awareness |

#### Environmental Storytelling

Failed quarantine: flashing amber emergency lights, discarded hazmat gear, heavy blast doors. The room should read as a desperate last stand before machines arrive.

